22;0.512 show the liquidity floor strengthening while institutional capital moves past last week\u0027s hawkish dot-plot noise. Intraday equity pullbacks remain mechanical mean-reversions unless funding stress reappears.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128197; Economic Calendar: 2026-06-22\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:12px; color:#64748b; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003eConfirmed macro windows for today\u0027s opening session. The draft Existing Home Sales entry was omitted because NAR\u0027s May release was last week and the next Existing Home Sales release is July 9. Eurozone flash consumer confidence and Treasury 13-week / 26-week bill auctions are confirmed for today.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eEST (US)\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eGMT+8 (Local)\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eImportance\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12p