u003c/strong\u003e Reduced post-meeting speech density would leave rates options desks to price the path with fewer official guideposts. Watch whether volatility stays compressed as this regime takes hold.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128200; Trading Strategy Note (ES Futures)\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Breakout Blueprint:\u003c/strong\u003e The May 1 expansion candle remains the macro lodestar. Compressed bond volatility plus lower Middle East risk premium keeps the structural allocation signal constructive.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTarget Horizons:\u003c/strong\u003e Structural projections remain unchanged, with the year-end Wall Street High Call still mapped to 8,447 to 8,477.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrder-Flow Execution:\u003c/strong\u003e During the Monday NY session, monitor 1.5k MotiveWave volume charts for mechanical stop-hunts. Do not fade all-time-high expansions; treat sharp VAL flushes as buy candidates only when absorption confirms.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(148,163,184,0.08);